The paper discusses power consumption modeling and prediction for a hybrid supercomputer, which involves hardware and software advances for high performance computing systems. This topic is closely related to several computer science sub-categories, including Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Architecture (cs.AR), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Software Engineering (cs.SE), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Among these sub-categories, cs.DC is the most relevant as it specifically deals with distributed and parallel computing systems, which are the focus of the paper. However, the other sub-categories are also relevant as they cover related topics such as computer architecture, system-level control, software engineering for large-scale systems, and optimization techniques using neural and evolutionary computing.
